item.title: What are those symbols shown in menus on Mac?
item.link: https://your-docusaurus-test-site.com/reference/blog/2021/09/11/What are those symbols shown in menus on Mac
item.guid: What are those symbols shown in menus on Mac?
item.description: Many app menus on your Mac show key combinations, such as Command symbol followed by N, next to certain menu options. The symbols in the key combinations represent special keyboard keys, called modifier keys.
